The Government of doe6.rfd @ maharashtra. Notify immediately at the email address gov.in.
4. Leave granted to the officer concerned for any reason without prior permission of the Government.

Don't do it. Also, in accordance with Rule-30 (c) of the MNS (Leave) Rules, 1981, any applications for leave of officers transferred by the original office shall be returned to the concerned officer by post at the original address. If the officer transferred to the original office sends applications for leave, the application will not be considered.

5. In case of non-appearance at the place of new posting immediately under the said transfer order or attempt to cancel the transfer by any kind of coercion, the act would be misconduct as it violates Rule 23 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct) Rules, 1979.
The concerned should note that disciplinary action will be taken against them as per the understanding.
This Government Order is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
